p345
aVThe hardest working man in show business lived a complicated life, but that was no reason to make his story hard to follow.
p346
aVThe screenplay bounces like a ping-pong ball from childhood to prison to manhood to early showbiz to late showbiz to Brown\u2019s mental problems.
p347
aVIt makes you want to scream out for a more linear approach.
p348
aVThere\u2019s nothing wrong with flashbacks and flash forwards.
p349
aVMost movies use at least a flashback or two to help tell their stories.
p350
aVBut, "Get On Up" turns Brown\u2019s life into popcorn.
p351
aVIt\u2019s like catching the kernels as they jump out of the pan.
p352
aVUnless you\u2019re already familiar with the singer\u2019s life, it\u2019s confusing.
