p1123
aVThe Catwoman\u2019s (Anne Hathaway) strange agenda is somehow connected to an overall master plot to bring Gotham City to its knees.
p1124
aVBane seems to have everything working to his advantage, but it\u2019s a grand mystery what he\u2019s up to.
p1125
aVThere are quite a few new characters in "The Dark Knight Rises," and that\u2019s the way Nolan likes it.
p1126
aVNolan\u2019s films are intelligent, complex and scream for repeat viewings.
p1127
aVWarner Brothers won\u2019t mind a bit.
p1128
aVJust look how the director\u2019s earlier films have fared at the box office.
p1129
aVI\u2019ve seen "Inception" at least a dozen times and could watch it again tonight without thinking twice.
p1130
aVGetting back to "The Dark Knight Rises," that\u2019s about as much description as you will find in my review.
p1131
aVGetting into the story is half the fun and I don\u2019t want to rob you of that pleasure.
p1132
aVIt\u2019s a story that demands your full attention.
p1133
aVBesides the stellar screenplay and amazing cast, you just have to MARVEL at how Nolan interweaves his characters.
